summary:
Tess is a Senior Solution Analyst at McKinsey with the Global Energy Perspectives team. She is passionate about decarbonisation and the energy transition. She combines her research and consulting experience with deep, unique knowledge from her past role as a target analyst for the Science Based Targets Initiative, the worlds leading climate initiative for validating GHG emission reduction strategies. She conducted in-depth assessments of corporate emissions reduction targets to ensure they align with the latest climate science and has a deep knowledge in carbon accounting and decarbonisation pathways.

She was previously an Environmental Affairs intern at the United Nations Environment Programme in Paris. She has a Master of Sustainability and Energy Management (MaSEM) from University of Bocconi - ranked globally as the Number 1 Master of Sustainable Development and Environmental Management by eduniversal. 

Tess has a Bachelor of International Business with Chinese Language from University College Dublin and spent a year studying at two of China's top universities - Renmin University and Zheijiang University. Her time spent in China, combined with a variety of international work, volunteer and study experiences - in the United States, Fiji, France, Italy and The Netherlands, have given her the ability to work in any society and with those from various cultures.
